# Workflow Phase Goals

- Every phase documented under `admin/internal/workflows/` must include an explicit `### Goals` checklist.
- Write the goal list before performing that phase's work.
- Goals must describe the phase's intended outcomes and decision gates, not implementation tasks from a later phase.
- Mark goals complete only when the phase evidence is recorded in the same workflow document.
- Do not advance to the next phase while required goals remain incomplete unless the workflow records the exception and user approval.
- Use `admin/internal/workflows/README.md` as the canonical process reference.
